pr_title: LB-1269: Separate follow listens from feed
pr_body:
# Problem

1) [LB-1269](https://tickets.metabrainz.org/browse/LB-1269)
According to the ListenBrainz Redesign, listen events (from followed users) are going to be separated from other feed events. This is to avoid shadowing due to high number of listens events when compared to all other events combined. 

2) Documentation was outdated.

# Solution

Procedure mentioned in ticket's description.

# Action

1) Created a new endpoint that just gives us listen events from followed users. No limit to how many listen events are given per user. Max items per get is 25 iff 25 listens are available. Else, all the listen in span of 7 days will be returned.
2) Updated documentation.

pr_body:
# Description

[LB-1270](https://tickets.metabrainz.org/browse/LB-1270)
New feature! Similar listens are listens from users who are similar to you!

# Action

Created a new function that gets similar users but with extra parameter "id". This "id" is used by get_all_listen_events, so we can create user_id_map. Now instead of deep embedding "similarity" into core functions, a new field is created in APITimelineEvent class that is null by default.

### Repercussions: 
Now every function that uses `APITimelineEvent` class to return responses will have an extra "similarity" dict associated with or in them. We can create a new class inheriting from `APITimelineEvent` to avoid this.

pr_title: Cleanup and subscribed to listen's list
pr_body:
Cleanup and added "listen" to socket listeners so that listen's list is updated automatically.
**Update:** Listens that are not submitted are now saved and bulk submitted at next available chance, i.e., when internet connection comes back or conditions are met.

pr_title: Fixes: Theme changes now retain state
pr_body:
## What's new?
1) When switching theme, the view models won't get destroyed meaning state will be retained. This also results in quick transition and gives accurate results.

2) YIM was not launching even with user logged in. Fixed that bug (cased by me).
